{meta: title Red Hen Hop}
{meta: artist Louvin Brothers}
{meta: writer Charlie Louvin and Ira Louvin}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]There's a little red hen lives down the street
She does the red-hen hop with a drumstick beat
A [F]chicken ain't a rooster if she can't make him [C]crow
She done the [G7]red-hen hop till she broke the roostin' [C]pole
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Now the little red hen don't know her age
But she don't worry 'bout turnin' gray
She does the [F]red-hen hop ever' time she lays an [C]egg
And if you [G7]eat her egg for breakfast
You' gonna do the hop all [C]day
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
When all the other chickens are feelin' kind o' blue
Now the little red hen knows what to do
She [F]gives out a party and they meet on a Saturday [C]night
They do the [G7]red-hen hop till the moon goes out o' [C]sight
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
One night when the party was a-gettin' kind o' cold
Said the little red hen give me room on the floor
She [F]grabbed her daddy cause he knows how to do the hop [C]right
They done the [G7]red-hen hop and they done it till broad day[C]light
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
Now the old black rooster was a-peepin' through the crack
Said I never seen the beast since the day I was hatched
[F]Momma never told me what the red-hen hop has [C]got
I'll do the [G7]red-hen hop till the day they throw me in the [C]pot
{end_of_verse}
